.TH "SITAR" "1" "April 2026" "sitar 0.9.0" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
sitar - System InformaTion At Runtime
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]sitar\f[R] [\f[I]COMMAND\f[R]] [\f[I]OPTION=VALUE\f[R] \&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]sitar\f[R] collects hardware, kernel, network, storage, security,
and package information from a running Linux system and renders it in
one or more structured output formats, including a machine-readable JSON
format aligned with the Machinery system description schema.
.PP
sitar must be run as root (uid=0).
It reads from /proc, /sys, and various system files, invoking external
tools (lsblk, ip, rpm, dpkg, etc.)
as needed.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]all\f[R]
Collect all system information.
Run check-consistency and find-unpacked cache generation.
Produce all output formats.
.TP
\f[B]check-consistency\f[R]
Check that RPM-declared configuration files have not been modified since
installation.
Write results to /var/lib/support/Configuration_Consistency.include.
May take 5-20 minutes.
.TP
\f[B]find-unpacked\f[R]
Find files below /etc that do not belong to any installed RPM.
Write results to /var/lib/support/Find_Unpacked.include.
May take 5-20 minutes.
.TP
\f[B]help\f[R]
Print usage information and exit 0.
.TP
\f[B]version\f[R]
Print version string and exit 0.
.TP
\f[B]debug\f[R]
Enable debug verbosity (equivalent to setting SITAR_DEBUG=1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]format=\f[R]_FORMAT_
Output format.
One of: \f[B]html\f[R], \f[B]tex\f[R], \f[B]sdocbook\f[R],
\f[B]json\f[R], \f[B]markdown\f[R], \f[B]all\f[R].
Default: all formats when using the \f[B]all\f[R] command, otherwise
html.
.TP
\f[B]outfile=\f[R]_PATH_
Write output to PATH.
Only valid when a single format is requested.
.TP
\f[B]outdir=\f[R]_PATH_
Write output files into directory PATH.
Created if it does not exist.
Default: /tmp/sitar-HOSTNAME-TIMESTAMP when multiple formats are
requested.
.TP
\f[B]limit=\f[R]_N_
Skip configuration files larger than N bytes.
0 means no limit.
Default: 700000.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Fatal error (not running as root, output file not writable).
.TP
\f[B]2\f[R]
Invocation error (bad arguments, unknown format).
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[B]/etc/sysconfig/sitar\f[R]
Configuration file.
Recognised keys: SITAR_OPT_FORMAT, SITAR_OPT_OUTDIR, SITAR_OPT_OUTFILE,
SITAR_OPT_LIMIT, SITAR_OPT_GCONF, SITAR_OPT_ALLCONFIGFILES,
SITAR_OPT_ALLSUBDOMAIN, SITAR_OPT_ALLSYSCONFIG, SITAR_OPT_EXCLUDE,
SITAR_OPT_LVMARCHIVE.
.TP
\f[B]/var/lib/support/\f[R]
Cache directory for check-consistency and find-unpacked results.
Drop *.include files here to extend the configuration file collection.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Collect all information and write to /tmp/sitar-report/:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sitar all outdir=/tmp/sitar-report
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Collect in JSON format only:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sitar format=json outfile=/tmp/snapshot.json
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Generate HTML report:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sitar format=html outdir=/var/tmp/sitar-html
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Pre-generate consistency cache:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sitar check-consistency
\f[R]
.fi
.SH INSTALLATION
.PP
sitar is distributed via the Open Build Service (build.opensuse.org).
.PP
For openSUSE/SLES:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
zypper install sitar
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
For Debian/Ubuntu:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
apt install sitar
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
For Red Hat/RHEL:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dnf install sitar
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
rpm(8), dpkg(1), lsblk(8), ip(8), systemctl(1)
